## Summary

Sprint 104 shipped four discrete improvements:

**1. CI build-verify workflow:**
- `.github/workflows/build-verify.yml` — `workflow_dispatch`-only matrix across
  `ubuntu-latest`, `windows-latest`, `macos-latest`; uploads unsigned artifacts
  per platform for manual testing; no signing, notarization, or publish.
- `package.json`: added `dist:mac` script (`electron-builder --mac zip`) — `zip`
  target avoids the darwin-only `dmg-license` dependency.
- Existing `release.yml` flagged as stale (runs `electron-builder -mwl` on
  `windows-latest` only — cannot produce valid macOS artifacts).

**2. Node version correction:**
- `package.json` `engines.node`: `>=18` → `>=22.12.0` (EBADENGINE warnings from
  `electron@42.5.2`, `@electron/get@5.0.0`, `utilium@3.4.0` all require >=22.12.0).
- `build-verify.yml` node-version: `20` → `22` in all three jobs.
- `test.yml` still pins `node-version 20` — flagged stale, left pending separate
  approval.

**3. Test portability fixes:**
- Fixed 4 hardcoded `/home/pawan/vscodeagent/Solution` absolute paths in
  `storageStatus.test.js`, `paths.test.js`, `sprint85-guard.test.js`,
  `sprint86-hotspot-guard.test.js` → `process.cwd()`-relative.
- `vitest.config.ts` `reportsDirectory`: `./coverage/ts` → `./coverage` (what all
  consumers — Sonar tooling, `check-coverage-failures.cjs`, 5 guard tests — expect).

**4. sprint91/92 guard timing fix:**
- Root cause: sprint91/92 guards read `coverage-summary.json` which is only written
  AFTER test execution completes; they cannot pass in the same invocation that
  generates their own coverage data.
- Added `vitest.test-ci.config.ts`: excludes sprint91/92 from `test:ci`; they run
  via `coverage:guarded` (coverage first, then guards as a separate post-coverage
  step).
- `sprint71`/`sprint72` guard assertions strengthened to check three independent
  components rather than one exact string.
- `better-sqlite3` native binary rebuilt for Linux (stale Windows-built `.node`
  dated June 15 caused 12 test files to fail with `invalid ELF header` — was
  masking true coverage numbers in all prior runs on this host).

**Verification:**
- `test:ci` exits 0 (297 files, 4923 tests after exclusions).
- `coverage:guarded` exits 0 (adds 2 guard files, total 299 files / 4943 tests).
- Real coverage confirmed: 94.96% stmts / 92.58% branch / 93.22% funcs / 95.11% lines.

